gr.interamerican.bo2.creation.creators
Class AbstractClassCreator

java.lang.Object
  gr.interamerican.bo2.creation.creators.AbstractClassCreator
All Implemented Interfaces:
ClassCreator
Direct Known Subclasses:
ImplementorForAbstractClasses, ImplementorForInterfaces
public abstract class AbstractClassCreator
extends Object
implements ClassCreator

Basic class composer. This composer can successfully create an implementation of an interface only if the interface is a java bean interface. If the interface has more methods than accessors, the method will fail.

mustImplementSerializable

protected boolean mustImplementSerializable()
Decides if the implementation will be Serializable. The default implementation of this method, returns true only if the class being created and analyzed by the analysis field is serializable.
Sub-classes can override this behavior.

Returns:
Returns true if the implementation class is going to be Serializable.

addBasicUpdaters

protected void addBasicUpdaters()
Adds the basic updaters.
The default basic updaters are:
  • One that sets the super type to according to the return value of the method supertype()
  • One that adds the fields that have been added with addFieldCode(strings)
  • One that adds the methods added with implementMethod(method, string)
  • One that adds interfaces returned by the interfaces() method.

    • getClassCompiler

    protected ClassCompiler getClassCompiler()
    Gets a class compiler that contains the updaters that have been added.

    Returns:
    Returns a class compiler
